51 3. (1) In a county granting a real property tax credit pursuant to this section, the
52 county and each political subdivision levying a real property tax on an eligible
53 taxpayer's homestead shall apply the county's or political subdivision's proportional
54 amount of such credit when calculating the eligible taxpayer's property tax liability for the
55 tax year. The total amount of the credit and the county's and each political subdivision's
56 proportional amount of the credit shall be noted in actual monetary value on the
57 statement of tax due sent to the eligible taxpayer by the county collector. The county
58 governing body or political subdivision's governing body may adopt reasonable procedures
59 in order to carry out the purposes and intent of this section, provided that neither the county
60 nor a political subdivision shall [not] adopt any procedure that limits the definition or scope
61 of eligible credit amount or eligible taxpayer as defined in this section.
62 (2) If an eligible taxpayer makes new construction and improvements to such eligible
63 taxpayer's homestead, the real property tax liability for the taxpayer's initial credit year shall
64 be increased to reflect the real property tax liability attributable to such new construction and
65 improvements.
66 (3) If an eligible taxpayer's homestead is annexed into a taxing jurisdiction to which
67 such eligible taxpayer did not owe real property tax in the eligible taxpayer's initial credit
68 year, then the real property tax liability for the taxpayer's initial credit year shall be increased
69 to reflect the real property tax liability owed to the annexing taxing jurisdiction.
70 4. For the purposes of calculating property tax levies pursuant to section 137.073, the
71 total amount of credits authorized [by] ina county pursuant to this section shall be considered
72 tax revenue, as such term is defined in section 137.073, actually received by the political
73 subdivision levying such tax.
